<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The example in docs <a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/zend.validate.writing_validators.html#zend.validate.writing_validators">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/…</a> and the following sentence ??"The call to _error() tracks a reason for validation failure. Since this class only defines one failure message, it is not necessary to provide _error() with the name of the failure message template."?? are outdated.</p>

<p>The possibility to call $this-&gt;_error() with no parameters isn't in ZF since 1.10 (<a href="http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/migration.110.html#migration.110.zend.validate.selfwritten">http://framework.zend.com/manual/en/…</a>)</p>

